Package ru.nsu.voronova

Class Diploma

java.lang.Object
ru.nsu.voronova.Diploma
public class Diploma extends Object
This class allows to create an analogue of the diploma received by students upon graduation from the university. In addition, this class provides methods for adding and retrieving information about a diploma.
Author:
Ann Voronova

  • Method Details

    • getQualifyingWork

      public QualifyingWork getQualifyingWork()
      Allows getting information about qualifying work in diploma. If qualifying work has not yet been added to the diploma, the method returns null.
      Returns:
      qualifying work.

    • addQualifyingWork

      public void addQualifyingWork​(String topic, Grade grade, String teacher) throws IncorrectGradeFormatException
      Adds qualifying work to diploma.
      Parameters:
      topic - - the topic of the qualifying work.
      grade - - the grade, which was specified for the qualifying work.
      teacher - - the surname of the scientific leader of the qualifying work.
      Throws:
      IncorrectGradeFormatException - - if incorrect grade was specified for the qualifying work.

    • addSubjectToSupplement

      public void addSubjectToSupplement​(String name, Grade grade, String teacher)
      Adds the result of attestation to the diploma supplement. For the same subject, only the result of the last attestation is taken into attestation.
      Parameters:
      name - - the name of the subject for which the certification was carried out.
      grade - - the grade the student received.
      teacher - - the teacher who gave the grade.

    • isHonorsDegree

      public boolean isHonorsDegree()
      Determines if the student can get an honors degree.
      Returns:
      true, if the student can get an honors degree, false otherwise.
